===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s-(l/r)e(j/ŋ)||squirrel, weasel}} (STEDT). Within Chinese, it may be related to {{och-l|狸}} (however, see there for more).

Compare {{cog|bo|སྲེ་མོང|'''སྲེ'''་མོང|weasel}}, {{cog|my|ရှဉ့်|tr=hrañ|t=squirrel}}, {{cog|lep|tr=să-myóŋ|t=marmot}}, {{cog|mjw|tr=iŋren|t=mongoose}} (< *''m-ren''), {{cog|kar-pro|*hliᴮ}} ({{zh-ref|Benedict, 1972}}; {{zh-ref|Handel, 2009}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007, 2009}}; STEDT). {{zh-ref|Hill (2019)}} disputes the {{cog|bo|-}} comparison on phonetic grounds.

